      "insight_id": "INSIGHT_REGION_GRID",
      "statement": "For the VLQ and four-top searches, the preselected sample is first split by lepton multiplicity (2l or 3l) and b-tag multiplicity (1, 2, or >=3), and then by HT and ETmiss requirements."
    },
    {
      "insight_id": "INSIGHT_VLQ_VS_4TOP_SPLIT",
      "statement": "Signal regions with at least three b-tagged jets are further split: relaxed HT plus high jet multiplicity is used for four-top sensitivity, while high HT plus lower jet multiplicity enhances VLQ sensitivity."
    },
    {
      "insight_id": "INSIGHT_FLAVOUR_HANDLING",
      "statement": "VLQ/four-top regions use inclusive lepton flavours to increase the statistics of the loosely selected samples used for reducible-background estimation, whereas the same-sign top search splits ee, e mu, and mu mu because the looser optimized selection provides enough statistics."
    },
    {
      "insight_id": "INSIGHT_SSTT_CHARGE_SELECTION",
      "statement": "The same-sign top search uses exactly two positive leptons, HT > 750 GeV, ETmiss > 40 GeV, at least one b-tagged jet, and |delta phi_ll| > 2.5."
